TEXT(&beginproblem);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

The solution of the linear system
\[
\begin{array}{rrcl}
2x &+3y &=& 3 \\
x &-y &=& 1 \\
\end{array}
\]

$BR
\(x=\) \{ ans_rule(6) \} and
EOT
&ANS(num_cmp("6/5"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(y=\) \{ ans_rule(6) \}.
EOT
&ANS(num_cmp("1/5"));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint: 
Only the right hand side makes this system different from the preceding one.
So proceed similarly.  I would enter my answers as fractions.
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Subtracting twice the second equation from the first gives the new equation
\(5y=1\).  Thus \(y=\frac{1}{5}\).  Substituting that value in the second
equation gives \(x-\frac{1}{5}=1\) or \(x=\frac{6}{5}\). 

EOT








